{
  "name": "Central Park",
  "formatted_address": "New York, NY, USA",
  "location": {
    "lat": 40.7825547,
    "lng": -73.9655834
  },
  "formatted_phone_number": "(212) 310-6600",
  "website": "https://www.centralparknyc.org/",
  "rating": 4.8,
  "reviews": [
    {
      "author_name": "Poorvajaa Raman",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113221534812225363967/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4ypRdm9ZNI1Yz3WupHniYkx7NKfh4jhCTMuOsdkinulvfJFo=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a week ago",
      "text": "So beautiful and peaceful for a relaxing afternoon.\nCan have a little picnic as well.\nGreat place for a family time or just to catch up with friends. Can even be very nice if you go alone.\nThe pond and the boathouse were beautiful.\nFood stalls were nice too!",
      "time": 1756474796,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "ilona",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113769119473757973387/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUasTC_gO_fDYBcO48yvNoecIJSXejvcR3MAsMTHy5WJRms1rXe=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "2 weeks ago",
      "text": "Central Park was such a nice experience. We started walking from the very bottom of the park and made our way all the way up to the top. It actually took us a few hours, but it never felt boring. There’s always something to see, whether it’s people playing music, kids running around, or just the calm nature around you. The park is really big, and it feels like a break from the city, even though you’re still in the middle of New York. The walking paths are easy to follow, and there are plenty of benches if you want to sit down and just take in the view. We stopped at a food stand along the way. The food was fine—not anything super special, but good enough for a quick snack while walking. It’s convenient because you don’t really need to leave the park to grab something. The lakes and bridges were really pretty, and the views of the skyline behind the trees are amazing. Overall, it was just a really nice way to spend a day in New York, and I’d definitely recommend taking the time to walk through the park if you can.",
      "time": 1755535729,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Nodirjon Yunusaliev",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106803333533675344194/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW96pqyKrPmfDaQFmwZ0MtBNq2tOG8O189CEW83HfGWXe07IFW7tw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "3 weeks ago",
      "text": "🌳 Central Park is truly the heart of New York City! A peaceful escape surrounded by skyscrapers, where you can walk, cycle, or just relax and enjoy nature. Beautiful gardens, lakes, bridges, and street performers make every visit unique. Perfect for a morning jog, picnic, or simply people-watching. A must-see for any NYC trip! 🗽✨",
      "time": 1755024848,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "Irina1983",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102574615888801994393/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUn6RNjdNDX8cAIm-cHguXoEJEczmx3Ssq457tcFRHJIo6aQK5qTA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "a month ago",
      "text": "Central Park: An Iconic Oasis in the Heart of NYC\nCentral Park isn't just a park; it's a living, breathing icon, a magnificent green heart beating in the concrete jungle of New York City. For locals and tourists alike, it's a place that transcends the ordinary, offering something truly special for everyone.\nThis sprawling, beautiful expanse is a testament to urban planning and natural beauty. Its sheer size is impressive, inviting endless exploration, and no matter where you wander, you're bound to stumble upon a delightful surprise. From the quiet serenity of the Conservatory Garden to the bustling energy around Bethesda Terrace, every corner tells a story.\nWhat truly sets Central Park apart is its vibrant cultural tapestry. It's a stage where art comes alive, with countless sculptures, memorials, and architectural gems scattered throughout. You'll often encounter impromptu performances, from street musicians to acrobats, adding to the park's dynamic atmosphere. It's also a fantastic place to connect with others; whether you're joining a pick-up game, sharing a bench with a stranger, or simply people-watching, new connections are always just around the corner.\nDuring my visit, I was captivated by Central Park's charm and beauty. While I didn't manage to explore every inch of it, what I did see left a lasting impression. It's a place where you can easily lose yourself for hours, whether you're seeking peaceful contemplation, an active adventure, or a dose of urban culture. I'm already looking forward to my next trip, planning to dedicate even more time to uncovering its many hidden treasures.\nCentral Park isn't just a destination; it's an experience, a must-visit for anyone looking to truly feel the pulse of New York City.\nI love it 😍",
      "time": 1752691203,
      "translated": false
    },
    {
      "author_name": "vedran mikulek",
      "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110411900358971310900/reviews",
      "language": "en",
      "original_language": "en",
      "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJDsvAXf5uAU7_GfsV_AhyV5Y1cljO2k9zMP_qvWf2uqr0ajdXO=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6",
      "rating": 5,
      "relative_time_description": "2 weeks ago",
      "text": "🌳 Central Park is the heart of New York City 💚.\nIt’s the perfect mix of nature 🌿, culture 🎶, and city vibes 🏙️. You can chill on the Great Lawn ☀️, row a boat on the lake 🛶, stroll across famous bridges 🌉, or just people-watch while enjoying a hot dog 🌭.\n\nEvery season feels magical — spring blossoms 🌸, summer picnics 🍉, autumn leaves 🍂, and winter ice skating ⛸️.\n\n⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ A must-see — NYC wouldn’t be NYC without it! ✨",
      "time": 1755979919,
      "translated": false
    }
